@Barry Ancona

I’m so groggy this morning, our last full day in Scandinavia, that I was glad it was an easy puzzle, but had I been in my normal milieu, it would have been too easy. But today, I’m just feeling cumulative exhaustion, and an easy one was welcome. 

Glad to have seen ODIN and THOR in the puzzle as a nod to this trip; I thought I saw something else from this area, too, but am too tired to go searching.

@Jeb
@Persephone

I've worked them out of order before, accidentally working the Sunday puzzle by accident late on a Saturday. It showed my streak at 1, but when I worked the Saturday puzzle either later that night or the next morning, my streak restored itself.

At other times, I've written the puzzle editors and asked them to fix my streak, for instance, when a completion didn't register because the wifi cut off as a plane was landing. It took them a few days but they eventually fixed it. Last time I tried this was a couple of years ago, though.

